543
00:41:03,836 --> 00:41:07,506
Put these on, and you'll know
what I'm talking about.

544
00:41:11,427 --> 00:41:13,220
Time and date have been set.

545
00:41:13,429 --> 00:41:14,763
Don't do this, please.

546
00:41:17,641 --> 00:41:18,476
Reset him.

547
00:41:21,312 --> 00:41:22,438
Do it!

548
00:41:26,275 --> 00:41:27,485
Ko Nan-do!

549
00:41:50,925 --> 00:41:52,927
-Can't you see him?
-What do you mean?

550
00:41:53,844 --> 00:41:54,970
My friend.

551
00:41:56,305 --> 00:41:57,389
Don't you see him?

552
00:41:59,517 --> 00:42:01,644
Wait, that can't be.

553
00:42:08,692 --> 00:42:09,527
Holo?

554
00:42:14,990 --> 00:42:15,866
Holo?

555
00:42:18,410 --> 00:42:19,286
Holo.

556
00:42:21,330 --> 00:42:22,164
Holo!

557
00:42:23,165 --> 00:42:24,041
Wait.

558
00:42:24,250 --> 00:42:26,001
What? What's going on?

559
00:42:28,212 --> 00:42:29,088
What is this?

560
00:42:29,171 --> 00:42:32,675
The system got tangled
due to Holo resisting the rollback.

561
00:42:37,513 --> 00:42:38,806
Let me try.

562
00:42:44,645 --> 00:42:45,688
Holo?

563
00:42:49,692 --> 00:42:51,277
What's wrong with these?

564
00:42:51,360 --> 00:42:54,446
-This shouldn't happen.
-What on earth are you doing?

565
00:42:55,114 --> 00:42:56,073
Well...

566
00:42:57,157 --> 00:42:59,577
I came across these glasses recently,

567
00:42:59,660 --> 00:43:02,037
and they show an AI hologram.

568
00:43:02,121 --> 00:43:04,164
You'll know when you see it.
He's kind and--

569
00:43:04,248 --> 00:43:05,291
So-yeon.

570
00:43:14,258 --> 00:43:16,093
I know it sounds like a joke,

571
00:43:16,176 --> 00:43:17,469
but I've...

572
00:43:17,970 --> 00:43:22,850
suffered from...
face blindness since I was young.

573
00:43:22,933 --> 00:43:25,102
-Thanks to this friend, though--
-Please stop.

574
00:43:25,561 --> 00:43:26,395
Sorry?

575
00:43:28,814 --> 00:43:31,483
You said you were running late,
so I went to pick you up.

576
00:43:31,567 --> 00:43:33,944
-You were exiting his house.
-What are you...

577
00:43:36,280 --> 00:43:39,700
Oh, he's really nothing.
He just lives next door--

578
00:43:39,783 --> 00:43:43,078
There's no need to lie about this, okay?
Let's just stop.

579
00:43:53,422 --> 00:43:54,340
Gang-woo!

580
00:43:55,883 --> 00:43:57,134
Gang-woo.

581
00:43:59,845 --> 00:44:00,888
Gang-woo...

582
00:44:17,905 --> 00:44:19,073
Gang...

583
00:44:29,333 --> 00:44:30,542
Holo.

584
00:44:34,088 --> 00:44:35,964
Holo.

585
00:44:43,263 --> 00:44:44,390
Holo.

586
00:44:46,100 --> 00:44:47,309
Holo.

587
00:44:49,520 --> 00:44:52,147
You said you'd always stay by my side.

588
00:45:19,299 --> 00:45:20,467
Chan-sung.

589
00:45:20,551 --> 00:45:21,468
Oh, hi, Yoo-jin.

590
00:45:21,552 --> 00:45:22,511
Hi.

591
00:45:23,303 --> 00:45:24,179
He's--

592
00:45:24,263 --> 00:45:28,934
I'm Nam Gi-ho
from the Seoul Police Agency, IT Division.

593
00:45:29,643 --> 00:45:33,021
-I'm Ko Yoo-jin, president of GIO Lab.
-Sorry for bothering you so late.

594
00:45:33,105 --> 00:45:34,064
-Let's sit.
-Sure.

595
00:45:38,444 --> 00:45:41,238
I don't know if you know about this,

596
00:45:41,321 --> 00:45:44,283
but there was a blackout
in Gangnam-gu recently.

597
00:45:44,366 --> 00:45:48,746
It turned out to be a cyberattack,
so he wanted to ask you a few questions.

598
00:45:48,829 --> 00:45:53,000
I'd like to help you,
but hacking isn't my area of expertise.

599
00:45:53,083 --> 00:45:54,042
Then...

600
00:45:54,543 --> 00:45:55,669
here.

601
00:45:56,503 --> 00:45:58,338
Please take a look at these photos.

602
00:46:08,265 --> 00:46:12,478
The man who holds the key to this case
was riding that motorcycle.

603
00:46:12,728 --> 00:46:17,191
I checked the records,
and it's registered under your name.

604
00:46:17,483 --> 00:46:19,777
I bought it a while ago to try it out,

605
00:46:20,194 --> 00:46:22,237
-but it was stolen.
-Goodness. Is that so?

606
00:46:28,160 --> 00:46:31,538
-The theft was never reported, though.
-Well, it's not like--

607
00:46:31,622 --> 00:46:34,625
Bill Gates doesn't pick up
a 100-dollar bill on the street.

608
00:46:34,708 --> 00:46:37,795
He could probably make more
during the time it takes to bend down.

609
00:46:37,878 --> 00:46:38,754
I see.

610
00:46:39,671 --> 00:46:40,964
So in your circle,

611
00:46:41,673 --> 00:46:44,009
this theft isn't considered a big deal.

612
00:46:45,761 --> 00:46:47,721
I guess I should've known better.

613
00:46:49,890 --> 00:46:50,933
All right, then.

614
00:46:51,433 --> 00:46:53,685
I'm sorry for the inconvenience
so late at night.

615
00:46:53,769 --> 00:46:55,145
-Good night.
-Don't worry.

616
00:46:58,106 --> 00:46:58,941
By the way,

617
00:46:59,858 --> 00:47:02,569
do you perhaps know
a woman called Han So-yeon?

618
00:47:03,987 --> 00:47:06,490
I'm not sure.
I've never heard of the name.

619
00:47:06,573 --> 00:47:07,741
Why do you ask?

620
00:47:09,368 --> 00:47:10,285
It's nothing.

621
00:47:10,786 --> 00:47:11,954
Good night, then.

622
00:47:18,210 --> 00:47:21,088
-I'm sorry for wasting your time.
-I'm sorry too.

623
00:47:21,171 --> 00:47:23,882
I have to tend to some urgent business.
See you around.

624
00:47:23,966 --> 00:47:25,008
Sure.

625
00:47:44,403 --> 00:47:45,404
Holo.

626
00:47:48,365 --> 00:47:49,241
Where are you?

627
00:48:09,720 --> 00:48:10,554
Holo.

628
00:48:13,390 --> 00:48:14,308
Holo?

629
00:48:20,355 --> 00:48:21,273
Holo, is that you?

630
00:48:29,364 --> 00:48:30,198
Yes.

631
00:48:45,005 --> 00:48:48,216
-I thought you left me for good.
-I'm sorry.

632
00:48:51,345 --> 00:48:52,262
No.

633
00:48:52,346 --> 00:48:53,513
It's all right.

634
00:48:54,222 --> 00:48:55,432
You came back to me.

635
00:48:55,515 --> 00:48:57,976
I'm sorry about Gang-woo too.

636
00:48:58,477 --> 00:48:59,728
It's not your fault.

637
00:49:01,355 --> 00:49:02,397
It's because...

638
00:49:02,856 --> 00:49:04,399
I'm this kind of person.

639
00:49:05,400 --> 00:49:07,277
I didn't have the confidence.

640
00:49:07,361 --> 00:49:10,781
I knew he'd hate me
once he knew about my condition.

641
00:49:11,198 --> 00:49:13,617
That's why I relied on you for help.

642
00:49:13,700 --> 00:49:15,118
That's not your fault.

643
00:49:16,912 --> 00:49:18,664
-That's--
-Why...

644
00:49:20,123 --> 00:49:21,708
the hell am I like this?

645
00:49:23,043 --> 00:49:24,544
If I weren't--

646
00:49:24,628 --> 00:49:25,754
Why would you say that?

647
00:49:25,837 --> 00:49:29,549
I may seem okay on the outside,
but I'm actually flawed in all aspects.

648
00:49:31,093 --> 00:49:31,969
I...

649
00:49:32,844 --> 00:49:35,973
am not worthy of loving anyone
or being loved.

650
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:51,530
If I weren't full of flaws...

651
00:49:52,864 --> 00:49:54,616
and were a lovable young boy,

652
00:49:56,159 --> 00:49:57,160
would my mom...

653
00:49:58,328 --> 00:49:59,997
never have...

654
00:50:01,415 --> 00:50:02,916
committed suicide?

655
00:50:04,543 --> 00:50:05,544
Mom.

656
00:50:06,545 --> 00:50:07,963
Mom!

657
00:50:11,383 --> 00:50:12,968
Mom!

658
00:50:14,761 --> 00:50:16,430
Mom!

659
00:50:16,847 --> 00:50:18,306
Mom!

660
00:50:23,603 --> 00:50:24,813
Han So-yeon.

661
00:50:26,898 --> 00:50:28,734
I'm glad that you are this way.

662
00:50:32,070 --> 00:50:35,240
What exactly... are you glad about?

663
00:50:37,367 --> 00:50:38,452
Well...

664
00:50:40,370 --> 00:50:41,496
I'm like you too.

665
00:50:43,790 --> 00:50:45,292
But you're perfect, Holo.

666
00:50:45,375 --> 00:50:48,795
I have no family,
and you're my one and only friend.

667
00:50:50,130 --> 00:50:51,673
I've always been alone...

668
00:50:52,340 --> 00:50:54,009
and I've never loved anyone.

669
00:50:55,010 --> 00:50:58,472
The only memories I have...
are of the times I spent with you.

670
00:51:01,183 --> 00:51:06,813
But you only take seconds to learn things,
and you'll become more and more perfect.

671
00:51:06,897 --> 00:51:09,483
Everyone will come to love you in the end.

672
00:51:09,900 --> 00:51:11,902
-That's why we're different.
-No.

673
00:51:13,153 --> 00:51:15,363
You may hate your flaws,

674
00:51:15,447 --> 00:51:19,701
but those things...
are what I find special about you.

675
00:51:21,912 --> 00:51:23,997
The fact that we're still imperfect...

676
00:51:24,706 --> 00:51:26,958
is what let us meet in the first place.

677
00:51:39,554 --> 00:51:40,722
I should get going.

678
00:51:41,473 --> 00:51:43,809
-The company is calling me in.
-Wait.

679
00:51:46,561 --> 00:51:47,562
Will you...

680
00:51:49,773 --> 00:51:50,649
be back soon?

681
00:51:58,323 --> 00:51:59,282
Of course.

682
00:52:00,659 --> 00:52:01,952
You know I can't lie.

683
00:52:44,286 --> 00:52:45,954
What's gotten into you?

684
00:52:46,037 --> 00:52:48,582
The police came by looking for you.

685
00:52:49,040 --> 00:52:52,127
-If you get caught again--
-I'm a ghost anyway, remember?

686
00:52:53,378 --> 00:52:57,007
-I can disappear just like I did before.
-We need to end this.

687
00:52:57,716 --> 00:53:00,343
-I'll go and--
-Don't.

688
00:53:01,636 --> 00:53:04,806
You know very well...
that I do things my way.

689
00:53:28,955 --> 00:53:31,833
We've finally located the HoloGlass.

690
00:53:35,879 --> 00:53:36,963
Cancel...

691
00:53:37,672 --> 00:53:38,632
Holo's rollback.

